• The user wants to sort a list. I should consider:

  - Time complexity requirements
  - Whether stability matters
  - Memory constraints
─ Worked for 0s ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
• Based on your requirements, here's a quicksort implementation:

  def quicksort(arr):
      if len(arr) <= 1:
          return arr
      pivot = arr[len(arr) // 2]
      left = [x for x in arr if x < pivot]
      middle = [x for x in arr if x == pivot]
      right = [x for x in arr if x > pivot]
      return quicksort(left) + middle + quicksort(right)
